The M.E. Commitment
---
s1-1-title
|||
You are a customer if you use any Mortal Economics products
---
s1-1-text
|||
Conventional wisdom suggests that when you use a free product, you <i>are</i> the product, right? Well, not here. Not all M.E. products are free, so a free product like <i>The Reference</i>, for example, is designed to operate at very low cost and it is financed by other, monetized, current and future M.E. products. The Reference is currently financed by myself.
---
s1-2-title
|||
Customers are never served third party ADs
---
s1-2-text
|||
Mortal Economics does not, and will never, serve third party ADs for revenue. M.E. will survive and thrive through the joy it sparks in paying customers, and word of mouth, or it will not survive at all. Give your ad blocker a well-deserved break.
<br><br>
At this time, M.E. does not purchase advertisements at all. This may change in the future, however, M.E. will not participate in conventional online advertising, which requires tracking and invading user privacy to keep the system churning.
<br><br>
M.E. is a business and will advertise its own products to customers.
---
s1-3-title
|||
Mortal Economics will not track customers outside of the M.E. domain and will use the least amount of behavioural data possible, created within the M.E. domain, to enhance M.E. products for the good of all customers.
---
s1-3-text
|||
<h4>Site Analytics</h4>
M.E. will not route customer web server traffic through third party analytics products.
<br><br>
M.E. will analyze its own web server traffic to determine how customers are interacting with M.E. products.
<br><br>
M.E. will use the IP address sent to all web servers by web browsers to determine which regions of the Earth customers are using our products from. Customer IP addresses will not be stored after the above process is completed, for each web request. A record correlating customers and customer IP addresses will never exist within the M.E. infrastructure.